Klan is a vibrant, dynamic, ever-expanding group of creatives operating under the musical branch of The Firm Entertainment. The formation of Klan was inspired by a desire for artists to work jointly in creating and promoting music. The group’s talents range from songwriting to music production. Klan now boasts a plethora of creative talent and has continued to grow ever-since. Follow the movement on the following links: Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/KoolKidsKult Twitter: @KlanFirm YouTube: The Firm Entertainment: Klan Soundcloud: https://soundcloud.com/k-l-a-n For further enquiries, contact Klan via E-mail: koolkidskultww@gmail.com

LaPartyX is beast when it comes to beats and bars. His music so effortlessly combines layers of great sounds with references and punchlines that are almost always bound to fly over your head. His talents are undeniable, making him an integral component of KLAN.

Nino De Loco is yet another great artist with strong affiliations to KLAN. His laid back style emulates the swagger in his artistry but boy oh boy can he get off! Nino's humility and work-ethic will make him a force to be reckoned with in the not so distant future.

Phil-Air is one of KLAN's most recent recruits and it's not too hard to see why. When it comes to lyrics and flow, Phil-Air is a relentless perfectionist whose rapping style is rarely flawed. Since joining KLAN, Phil-Air has lent a hand in producing under the alias: MULK.
Rhythm and Poetry. A genre of popular music of US black origin in which words are recited rapidly and rhythmically over an instrumental backing.

Raven Wray is a gem of an artist, with the ability to bring life to tracks like no other. His charisma always shines through from the beginning to the end of every song he is featured on. Raven Wray's sound possessed a smoothness and clarity that draws the listener in, especially when utilized on the hook.

Rhythm and Blues, often abbreviated as R&B or RnB, is a genre of popular African-American music that originated in the 1940s. The term was originally used by record companies to describe recordings marketed predominantly to urban African Americans, at a time when "urbane, rocking, jazz based music with a heavy, insistent beat" was becoming more popular.

Russel Sips has the touch of Midas. He is the balancing force of KLAN and every song he is featured on. His know-how is unprecedented, allowing him to give meaning and relevance to tracks in a way that transcends even the most experienced of great artists.

Trap music is a subgenre that originated during the 1990s from Southern hip hop in the Southern United States. It is typified by its ominous lyrics and sound that incorporate double or triple-time division hi-hats, heavy kick drums from an 808 synthesizer, layered synthesizers, and "cinematic" strings. In recent years it has been incorporated with electronic dance music (EDM) by artists who have remixed and made trap songs with more EDM-like aspects.

Vanity Of Man is one of the founders of KLAN. He is also a member of the Royal Roots collective. His poetic way with words combined with a consistently unique sound make him a natural front-runner when it comes to the production of quality music.

Vicci Martini is like a one-man band that is simply in a league of its own. He can sing and rap, and he produces his own craft! There should be an image of him next to the definition of the word 'range'.

World music is a genre encompassing many different styles of music from around the globe, which includes many genres including some forms of Western music represented by folk music, as well as selected forms of ethnic music, indigenous music, neotraditional music, and music where more than one cultural tradition, such as ethnic music and Western popular music, intermingle.

item.title: KLAN - Mount Purp (Mixtape)
item.dc:creator: Nkosie199
item.content:encoded: The Firm Entertainment is proud to announce the successful release of the KLAN mixtape - Mount Purp. Mount Purp is a representation of the hard work put in by the KLAN collective from January 2017 until it's release on the 26th of October 2017. The mixtape tells the story of a group of individuals each similarly indoctrinated by a sense of group-think. The featured artists give you a strong sense of what it is like seeing through their eyes; through tales their late night jam sessions, depressing thoughts, and unconventional passions and moral beliefs.
